The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Bengal girls shine

 A STAFF REPORTER 

Calcutta: Bengal girls emerged overall champions in the inter-zonal athletics meet held in Meerut from Friday to Sunday. 

According to information reaching here, Bengal?s Lavina Khatun was adjudged the best girl athlete, while compatriot Hari Shankar Roy was declared the best athlete among boys. 

Meanwhile, four Bengal athletes ? Pinki Pramanik, Lavina Khatun, Hari Shankar Roy and Rahmatullah Mollah ? were selected to represent the country in the Youth Commonwealth Games to be held in Australia next month. 

